"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Patient.ID)\nFROM Patient\nJOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID\nWHERE Laboratory.RNP IN ('-', '0')\nAND Patient.Admission = '+';\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct patients who have a normal level of anti-ribonuclear protein (RNP) and have been admitted to the hospital. The normal level of RNP is defined as either '-' (negative) or '0', and admission to the hospital is indicated by the Admission column having a value of '+'."